<subSubSection lastPageId="60" lastPageNumber="61" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1436,1824,1920]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,466,1824,1849]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis box="[199,372,1824,1849]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" reason="1">Redescription.</emphasis>
Female
</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[480,584,1824,1848]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">holotype</typeStatus>
). PL 4.2, PW 3.3, AW 2.0, OL 4.8, OW 3.0. Spination of palp and legs: palp 131, 000, 1211, 1013; femora I p021, d111, r111, II p112(3), d111, r111, III p112, d111, r112, IV p112, d111, r001; patellae I–II 000, III–IV 001; tibiae I missing, II v22222, III p11, d111(11), r11, v222, IV p11, d111, r11, v222;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1436,1932,2028]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">metatarsi I missing, II v222, III p112, d01(0)0, r112, v222, IV p112, d010, r112, v12212. Chelicerae with 3 promarginal, 5 retromarginal teeth, with elongated field (distally ending as single row) with 25–30 denticles. Retromargin of chelicerae close to fang base with 5 bristles.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,151,535]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
Copulatory organ as in diagnosis (
<figureCitation box="[607,769,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 266–269. 266–268" captionStartId="59.[151,263,1685,1708]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,733,1663]" captionTargetId="figure-283@59.[152,1435,721,1664]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURES 266–269. 266–268 Amauropelma fungifer (Thorell 1890), holotype female from Pulau Penang, Malaysia. 269 Ctenus valvularis Hasselt 1882, holotype(?) female from Sumatra, Indonesia. 266, 269 Epigyne, ventral. 267 Epigyne, posterior. 268 Vulva, dorsal. [269 modified after Hasselt 1882]." pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Figs 266–268</figureCitation>
, 274. Epigynal field with 3 slit sense organs anterior to epigynal plate (only seen in dissected epigyne). Posterior part of epigynal plate narrow with distinct lateral margins. Distal part of lateral teeth posteriorad. Internal duct system with two round chambers as spermathecae, one large and one small; widely separated from each other; fertilisation ducts mediad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,151,535]" box="[199,1436,295,319]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
Colour (Figs 270–273). Faded in 
<typeStatus box="[573,671,295,319]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">holotype</typeStatus>
with remnants of dark lateral longitudinal bands on dorsal prosoma.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,151,535]" box="[199,392,332,356]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,266,332,356]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,151,535]" box="[199,901,367,392]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,367,392]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" reason="1">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[608,656,368,392]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<figureCitation box="[762,861,367,391]" captionStart="FIGURE 179" captionStartId="43.[151,249,1203,1226]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,193,1182]" captionTargetId="figure-373@43.[159,1428,193,1182]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 179. Records of Amauropelma spp. in South and Southeast Asia. 1–3 India (1 Shimla, Himachal Pradesh; 2 Dhanolti, Uttar Pradesh, 3 Rongdanggai, Meghalaya). 4–6 Laos (4 Ban Tavan/Nam Ha protected area, Luang Nam Tha; 5 Nong Khiao, Luang Prabang; 6 Nam Khan, Luang Prabang). 7 Pulau Penang, Malaysia." pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Fig. 179</figureCitation>
: 7).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,151,535]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,404,428]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Note.</emphasis>
The small size and colour pattern and especially the shape of the epigynal plate as well as the patellar spination support that this species belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Raven, Stumkat &amp; Gray" authorityYear="2001" box="[779,937,440,464]" class="Arachnida" family="Ctenidae" genus="Amauropelma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[779,937,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Amauropelma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It was compared in the original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Thorell" box="[158,306,476,500]" firstAuthor="Thorell" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="269 - 383" refId="ref32280" refString="Thorell, T. (1890) Arachnidi di Pinang raccolti nel 1889 dai Signori L. Loria e L. Fea. Annali des Museo civico di storia naturale Genova, 30, 269 - 383." type="journal article" year="1890">Thorell 1890</bibRefCitation>
) with 
<taxonomicName authority="Hasselt 1882" authorityName="Hasselt" authorityYear="1882" box="[378,726,476,500]" class="Arachnida" family="Ctenidae" genus="Ctenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valvularis">
<emphasis box="[378,574,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Ctenus valvularis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hasselt" box="[581,726,476,500]" firstAuthor="Hasselt" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="1 - 56" refId="ref31005" refString="Hasselt, A. W. M. van (1882) Araneae. In: Weth, P. J. (Ed.), Midden Sumatra IV. 3 de Aflevering Naturlijke Historie, Leiden, 11 A, 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="1882">Hasselt 1882</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[794,844,476,499]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Java</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[897,994,476,500]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
. For comparative purposes, the original illustration by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hasselt" box="[314,478,511,535]" firstAuthor="Hasselt" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="1 - 56" refId="ref31005" refString="Hasselt, A. W. M. van (1882) Araneae. In: Weth, P. J. (Ed.), Midden Sumatra IV. 3 de Aflevering Naturlijke Historie, Leiden, 11 A, 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="1882">Hasselt (1882)</bibRefCitation>
is depicted here (
<figureCitation box="[676,775,511,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 266–269. 266–268" captionStartId="59.[151,263,1685,1708]" captionTargetBox="[162,1426,733,1663]" captionTargetId="figure-283@59.[152,1435,721,1664]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURES 266–269. 266–268 Amauropelma fungifer (Thorell 1890), holotype female from Pulau Penang, Malaysia. 269 Ctenus valvularis Hasselt 1882, holotype(?) female from Sumatra, Indonesia. 266, 269 Epigyne, ventral. 267 Epigyne, posterior. 268 Vulva, dorsal. [269 modified after Hasselt 1882]." pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Fig. 269</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
